  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Industry Capacity to Implement Ethical Recruitment Models in Viet Nam and Nepal to Protect Migrant Workers in South Korean Businesses&apos; Supply Chains</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will help build the capacities of government and business stakeholders in the Republic of Korea, Viet Nam and Nepal to translate private sector commitments into effective ethical recruitment schemes and multi-stakeholder action plans to reduce the risk of human trafficking and slavery. IOM&apos;s International Recruitment Integrity System (IRIS), and the Corporate Responsibility in Eliminating Slavery and Trafficking (CREST) initiative will provide relevant platforms on which to build communities in practice.</narrative>
  </description>
